parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS brakes can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and property damage.
symptoms: The ABS brakes fail to engage
requiring extreme pressure to lock up the front wheels
or the brakes fail to function altogether
leading to a loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause issues with the braking system, leading to a loss of vehicle control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine knocks or makes a loud noise after warming up
indicating a problem with the master cylinder.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling can cause the vehicle to shut off without warning, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle starts in an unusual manner
requiring multiple attempts to turn the key
moving the shift lever
and opening and closing doors; the vehicle shuts off while driving
mostly at low speeds (25-35 mph)
but occasionally at higher speeds (55-65 mph); the vehicle restarts immediately after shutting off; the check engine light appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to accelerate, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or fails to accelerate
the engine hesitates or stumbles
the vehicle has difficulty starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The issue with the fuel tank or suspension can cause the vehicle to lean to one side, affecting its stability and handling, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle leans to one side
uneven fuel tank filling
difficulty maintaining vehicle balance.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Wear of Upper and Lower Ball Joints
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature wear of upper and lower ball joints can cause uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and increased risk of accidents due to loss of control.
symptoms: Unusual noises or vibrations from the front suspension
uneven tire wear
loose or wandering steering
reduced vehicle stability.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause engine overheating, coolant leakage, and engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potential engine failure.
symptoms: Engine overheating
coolant leakage
white smoke or sweet-smelling smoke from the exhaust
engine misfires
reduced engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping or failure can cause loss of power, unexpected acceleration, or stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle experiences sudden or unexpected acceleration
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission makes unusual noises or vibrations
the vehicle has difficulty shifting into gear.
